FBIS4-66109 "drweu103__a94027" FBIS-WEU-94-103-A Daily Report 27 May 1994 ANNEX Germany Trade Unions Nominate Schulte for DGB Chairmanship Trade Unions Nominate Schulte for DGB Chairmanship AU2205140694 Hamburg DPA in German 1221 GMT 22 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2205140694 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] Berlin -- Dieter Schulze, 54, has been nominated as the official candidate to succeed Heinz-Werner Meyer, the leader of the German Trade Union Federation [DGB] who died two weeks ago. The chairmen of the individual trade unions decided at a special session today to present Schulte at the DGB Congress scheduled to take place in Berlin between 13 and 17 June as candidate for the chairmanship. DPA learned this from participants in the special session. The 54-year-old official is a member of the Executive Committee of the Metal Workers Trade Union and responsible for the steel industry and for codetermination. The trade union chairmen rejected a crucial vote at the DGB congress between Schulte and DGB Deputy Chairwoman Ursula Engelen-Kefer.
